# Onsen Robot — Quality Check Procedure

Run every section below in order. Report PASS / FAIL / WARN per item. Stop a section early only if the failure makes the rest of it meaningless.

---

## 1. Python static analysis

```bash
# Install checkers if missing (inside the repo, not system-wide)
pip install --quiet ruff mypy 2>/dev/null

# Style + logic errors — both packages
ruff check src/onsen_ai_worker src/onsen_dummy_robot

# Type check AI worker (the more complex node)
mypy src/onsen_ai_worker/onsen_ai_worker/ai_worker_node.py \
     --ignore-missing-imports --no-strict-optional
```

PASS criteria:
- `ruff` exits 0 (no errors, warnings acceptable)
- `mypy` reports no `error:` lines (notes/warnings OK)

---

## 2. Topic contract consistency

The publisher side (dummy_stream_node.py) and subscriber side (ai_worker_node.py + app.js) must agree on every topic name and message type. Check these pairs:

| Topic | Publisher type | Subscriber(s) |
|---|---|---|
| `/camera/front/image_raw` | `sensor_msgs/Image` | ai_worker_node |
| `/camera/front/image_raw/compressed` | `sensor_msgs/CompressedImage` | app.js via rosbridge |
| `/scan` | `sensor_msgs/LaserScan` | app.js |
| `/odom` | `nav_msgs/Odometry` | app.js |
| `/joint_states` | `sensor_msgs/JointState` | app.js |
| `/arm/state` | `std_msgs/String` (JSON) | app.js |
| `/arm/action` | `std_msgs/String` (JSON) | dummy_stream_node |
| `/cmd_vel` | `geometry_msgs/Twist` | dummy_stream_node |
| `/detected_objects` | `std_msgs/String` (JSON) | app.js |
| `/task_plan` | `std_msgs/String` (JSON) | app.js |
| `/robot/events` | `std_msgs/String` (JSON) | app.js |
| `/robot/control_mode` | `std_msgs/String` (JSON) | app.js |

```bash
grep -n "create_publisher\|create_subscription" \
  src/onsen_dummy_robot/onsen_dummy_robot/dummy_stream_node.py \
  src/onsen_ai_worker/onsen_ai_worker/ai_worker_node.py

grep -n "new ROSLIB.Topic\|messageType" frontend/js/app.js
```

PASS criteria: every topic in the table above appears in both publisher and subscriber with matching message type strings.

---

## 3. JSON schema spot-check (std_msgs/String payloads)

Each JSON topic has an implicit schema. Verify the keys are consistent between producer and consumer:

```bash
# arm/state producer keys vs consumer keys
grep -n "arm_state\|state.*cycle\|success_prob" \
  src/onsen_dummy_robot/onsen_dummy_robot/arm_state_machine.py
grep -n "arm-state-val\|arm-cycle\|arm-prob\|armState" frontend/js/app.js

# task_plan keys
grep -n '"next_action"\|"reason"\|"target_object_id"' \
  src/onsen_ai_worker/onsen_ai_worker/ai_worker_node.py
grep -n "task-action\|task-reason\|taskPlan" frontend/js/app.js

# detected_objects keys
grep -n '"objects"\|"confidence"\|"class"\|"bbox"' \
  src/onsen_ai_worker/onsen_ai_worker/ai_worker_node.py
grep -n "\.confidence\|\.class\|detect" frontend/js/app.js
```

PASS criteria: every key written by the publisher is read by the consumer (no silent typos).

---

## 4. Docker build validation

```bash
# Dry-run the ROS workspace build (no daemon needed)
docker build --target=build . --no-cache 2>&1 | tail -30
# If no multi-stage, just validate the Dockerfile parses:
docker build -f Dockerfile . --dry-run 2>/dev/null || \
  docker buildx build -f Dockerfile . --no-cache --progress=plain 2>&1 | grep -E "^#|ERROR|WARN" | head -40

# Frontend image
docker build -f frontend/Dockerfile frontend/ --no-cache 2>&1 | tail -20
```

PASS criteria: both builds exit 0. WARN on cache-only failures if network is unavailable.

---

## 5. Docker Compose schema validation

```bash
docker compose config --quiet && echo "compose: VALID" || echo "compose: INVALID"
docker compose config 2>&1 | grep -iE "warn|error|invalid"
```

Check that:
- All services that need ROS have `<<: *ros-env`
- `ai_worker` depends_on `dummy_robot`
- `frontend` depends_on `rosbridge`
- `rosbag_recorder` and `rosbag_player` are under `profiles: [record]` / `profiles: [play]`

---

## 6. Upload endpoint reachability (static analysis)

Verify the upload path is wired end-to-end without running Docker:

```bash
# nginx proxy block exists
grep -n "api" frontend/nginx.conf

# ai_worker starts HTTP server
grep -n "_start_upload_server\|HTTPServer\|5000" \
  src/onsen_ai_worker/onsen_ai_worker/ai_worker_node.py

# frontend calls /api/upload
grep -n "api/upload\|setupUploadButton" frontend/js/app.js
```

PASS criteria: all three locations confirm the path exists.

---

## 7. Frontend JS sanity

```bash
# No obvious undefined references to DOM IDs that don't exist in HTML
node -e "
const fs = require('fs');
const html = fs.readFileSync('frontend/index.html','utf8');
const js   = fs.readFileSync('frontend/js/app.js','utf8');
const ids  = [...html.matchAll(/id=\"([\w-]+)\"/g)].map(m=>m[1]);
const gets = [...js.matchAll(/getElementById\(['\"]+([\w-]+)['\"]+\)/g)].map(m=>m[1]);
const missing = gets.filter(id => !ids.includes(id));
if (missing.length) { console.log('MISSING IDs:', missing); process.exit(1); }
else console.log('All getElementById calls resolve — PASS');
"
```

PASS criteria: script exits 0.

---

## 8. Arm state machine completeness

```bash
# Every state the UI can request must be handled by the state machine
grep -n "data-state=" frontend/index.html
grep -n "ArmState\.\|force_state\|HOME\|SEARCH\|GRIP\|LIFT\|DROP" \
  src/onsen_dummy_robot/onsen_dummy_robot/arm_state_machine.py
```

PASS criteria: every `data-state` value in the HTML appears as an `ArmState` enum member.

